The paper discusses the implementation of a data science platform for healthcare and precision medicine research, which involves data acquisition, storage, and analysis. This suggests that the paper could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories, including cs.DB (databases), cs.CY (computational biology), cs.LG (machine learning), cs.CE (computational engineering), and cs.HC (human-computer interaction). However, given the focus on big data and real-time analytics, cs.DB and cs.CY are the most likely sub-categories. The use of open-source technologies also suggests a potential fit with cs.LG and cs.CE, while the healthcare context points to cs.HC as a possible sub-category.
